 Patients are assigned to an arm accordingly to their needs: class 1 with light therapeutic education, class 2 with moderate education, class 3 with heavy education.

 Assignement is based on the first education diagnosis during hospitalization time.

 Quality of life and patient's knowledge are regularly evaluated through questionnaires.

